Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1706
H.P. 1141 House of Representatives, April 17, 2025
Representation for Indigent Clients in Custody
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WARREN of Scarborough.
Cosponsored by Senator LAWRENCE of York and
Representatives: BOYER of Poland, HASENFUS of Readfield, MATHIESON of Kittery,
MILLIKEN of Blue Hill, MITCHELL of Cumberland, SALISBURY of Westbrook, SAYRE
of Kennebunk, SKOLD of Portland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 15 MRSA ยง810, sub-ยง4 is enacted to read:
3 4. Docketing of assignment of counsel. Assignment of competent defense counsel
4 pursuant to subsection 2 or 3 must be docketed within 24 hours of the assignment,
5 excluding Saturdays, Sundays and holidays, if the defendant is incarcerated at the time of
6 the assignment.
7 SUMMARY
88 This bill requires assignment of competent defense counsel to an accused person who
99 is indigent within 24 hours of such assignment if the accused is incarcerated.
